== Original research ==
I don't see the term "Battle in Shakhtarsk Raion" used in any source. Russian and Ukrainian Wikipedias also don't know anything about it, it's within the larger war in Donbass. There's an article about a specific [[:ru:Бои за Саур-Могилу (2014)|battle of Savur-Mohyla]], but this article has a much larger scope.--[[Special:Contributions/5.0.245.237|5.0.245.237]] ([[User talk:5.0.245.237|talk]]) 21:22, 12 August 2014 (UTC)
::It isn't a proper name, it is a [[WP:NDESC]] for events in Shaktarsk Raion. Most of these locations are very close to each other, such as Marynivka, Dmytrivka, and Savur-Mohyla. They are not going to each get an article, and fighting often moves between them. That's why lumping them together makes sense. Individual battle articles would never meet notability guidelines. [[User:RGloucester|<span style="font-family:Monotype Corsiva;font-size:12pt;color:#000000">RGloucester </span>]] — [[User talk:RGloucester|☎]] 21:42, 12 August 2014 (UTC)
:::Doesn't seem like [[WP:NDESC]] to me. More like [[WP:OR]] and [[WP:SYNTH]].--[[Special:Contributions/196.207.200.47|196.207.200.47]] ([[User talk:196.207.200.47|talk]]) 00:50, 13 August 2014 (UTC)
::::I don't understand what is "original research" about it. There has been fighting across Shakhtarsk Raion, as shown in sources. The fighting is therefore documented in an article that deals with that region. [[User:RGloucester|<span style="font-family:Monotype Corsiva;font-size:12pt;color:#000000">RGloucester </span>]] — [[User talk:RGloucester|☎]] 00:57, 13 August 2014 (UTC)
:::::I agree with RGloucester; it's a descriptive name. That is not original research. [[User:Dustin V. S.|<span style="color:green; font-family:Times New Roman">''Dustin''</span>]]&nbsp;[[User talk:Dustin V. S.|(<span style="color:green; font-family:Times New Roman">talk</span>)]] 01:04, 13 August 2014 (UTC)

